	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I thought the categories clear, but maybe I don't understand who's an authority here.<br /><br /><br />For the purposes of judging/competition:<br /><br />1. NROM (&lt;= 32k PRG, 8k CHR ROM or RAM, fixed H or V mirroring, no other mapper features)<br />2. Anything else<br /><br /><br />Independent of this is whether or not it could go on the compo cartridge:<br /><br />1. Compliant with <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/INES_Mapper_028" class="postlink">the compo cartridge mapper</a> and size restriction (&lt;= 64k PRG+CHR ROM)<br />2. Not compliant

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


